Etymology[edit]

From sēnsus (“perception, feeling”) + faciō (“do, make”)

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /senˈsi.fi.koː/, [sẽːˈsɪ.fɪ.koː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /senˈsi.fi.ko/, [sɛnˈsiː.fi.kɔ]

Verb[edit]

sēnsificō (present infinitive sēnsificāre, perfect active sēnsificāvī, supine sēnsificātum); first conjugation

  1. I make sensible, endow with sensation
